Hi! this is Kiwi sweet jelly. hi^^
The basic red bean sweet jelly is good, but I added kiwi to make it more colorful. 
The process of making it is simple, but you have to remember some points.
After making green tea for the first time, pour it into a pan and don't harden it too much. If you harden too much, the milk and green tea will fall off without sticking together.
I failed a lot because of this. It's the part where the bulldozers really struggled to throw the mold into the kitchen ã…œã…œ

Also, please don't use the kiwi fruit too big. If it's too big, it'll come out on top of a pan. The visual is not pretty!
Pour over the fruit, not over the green tea.

Packaging is an important part. I've also tested it several times for packaging. You have to put it in a box so that the back side is up to get rid of the moisture in the fruit. It's very moisturizing, so if you put it on top, it'll get really sticky. Make sure the back is up!
Make and eat within 1-2 days and refrigerate. 
We didn't have any other fruits, so we did kiwi first. I'll make another one if there are other fruits suitable for the sheep. Thank you very much.

* Tools and recipe
pan(20*7*4)
No big kiwi 3
spatula
Agar powder(greentea:5g, milk5g)
water(used in greentea jelly: 120g)
Beanpaste 190g  per milk and green tea
Sugar (50g per milk and green tea)
green tea water(you can use Wilton Moss green as well , 3g+water2T)
milk 130g

ğŸ“Hi! ğŸ“
this is Strawberry sweet jelly.
It's made with Pink cactus powderğŸ˜
As I told you then, you must remember some pointsğŸ’š
Don't let it harden too much by pouring it into a container after making it for the first time. 
If you harden it too much, the white and pink colors don't stick together.
Don't forget to check this part because I've failed several times!

The kiwi is made of a mold, but I thought I could use an airtight container at home, so I tried it.
I'm more comfortable using an airtight containerğŸ˜ I wrote down the size below, so try using the container at home.

You know the packaging is important, right?
This is a fruits jelly that is not a regular red bean jelly. Make sure that the back side is up from the inside out. 
That way, the water in the fruit will be less. When the water comes out from straqberry, the box becomes very sticky.
Eat  jelly without fruit for about 5 days and jelly with fruit within 1-2 days, both of which must be refrigerated. 
Thank youğŸ’š


â£ï¸Tools and recipeâ£ï¸
pan(15*10*4)
strawberry 6
Agar powder(pink cactus :5g, milk5g)
water(used in pink cactus jelly: 95g)
Beanpaste 150g per milk and pink cactus
Sugar (40g per milk and pink cactus)
pink cactus water(you can use Wilton Pink as well , 4g+water2T)
milk 100g

ğŸ“
1)put water and agar powder in pot.
2)cut strawberry and dry water.
3)put cactus powder in water.
4)Boil and melt sugar.
5)put bean paste and mix.
6)put cactus water and mix.
7)pour 6) in container.
8)put strawberry on jelly after 3-4minutes.
9) put agar powder in milk and make milk jelly again like cactus jelly.
10) after 5minutes, pour milk jelly on strawberry.
11)Chill more 1hour.
12)cut it and wrapped. keep it in refrigerator and eat it within 2days.

Hi, everyoneğŸ˜
Today, I made a sweet and chewy banana rice cake.
It's a look like real banana rice cake, and you can enjoy it sweetly with custard cream inside.

I hope you enjoy the video of making the banana rice cake. I'll be back with another video.
Thank you very much ğŸ™‚

â£ï¸Tools and recipeâ£ï¸

1. Rice cake:
Rice powder 4cup(200ml cup)
Gglutinous rice flour 1.5cup(200ml cup)
Sugar 5T(15ml spoon)
Yellow powder
Banana syrup1ts(5ml spoon)
Water 7T(15ml spoon)
7 banana pans 
Rice pot

2. Custard cream
Piping bag
2 yolks
Sugar 40g
Flour 12g
Milk100g
Banilla bean paste1ts
Pot
Spatualla
Seive

ğŸŒHow to make cakeğŸŒ

1. Custard cream
1) Add sugar to the yolk and mix until it is milky white.
2) Add flour.
3) Put vanilla bean paste in warm milk and mix 2).
4) Boil it over high heat. Continue stirring with a whisk.
5) Put it on a platter and cover it with plastic wrap and cool it down.
6) Put it down on a sieve and put it in a piping bag for use

2. Banana Rice cake
1) Mix glutinous rice with rice and mix it with banana syruo and water.
2) Add yellow powder.
3) Sift out and add sugar.
4)Press it in a small amount in a banana pan. Put a small amount on top of it and make place for the cream.
5) Add custard cream. Don't put too much in. It's going to explode
6) Put the powder on top of it and put it in a steamer. When the water boils, put it in a steamer and steam it over high heat for 20 minutes. Put the cloth up before you cover it.
7) Steam it all and gently remove it from the pan.
8) Please eat it within the day or keep it frozen.â€‹
